shatter /ˈʃætə/

(shattering,shattered,shatters) 

1. V-T/V-I If something shatters or is shattered , it breaks into a lot of small pieces. 粉碎 

例： ...safety glass that won't shatter if it's broken. …安全玻璃即使破了也不会粉碎。 

例： The car shattered into a thousand burning pieces in a 200 mph crash. 这辆轿车在时速200英里的碰撞中裂成了数以千计燃烧着的碎片。 

2. shattering N-UNCOUNT 粉碎 

例： ...the shattering of glass. …玻璃的粉碎。 

3. V-T If something shatters your dreams, hopes, or beliefs, it completely destroys them. 粉碎 (梦想、希望、信仰等) 

例： A failure would shatter the hopes of many people. 一次失败会粉碎很多人的希望。 

4. V-T If someone is shattered by an event, it shocks and upsets them very much. 严重打击 

例： He had been shattered by his son's death. 儿子的死使他很受打击。 

5.  →  see also shattered , shattering

